1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:38,780
[Lost Identity]

3
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:45,509
[Episode 6]

4
00:01:47,150 --> 00:01:48,110
Ou Xiao'an said

5
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,330
there was a mole inside the Chongqing Station

6
00:01:50,330 --> 00:01:52,020
who was making Ohashi's progress faster

7
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:53,670
and slowing us down.

8
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,030
We all heard it during the interrogation.

9
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,729
Have you forgotten it already?

10
00:01:57,729 --> 00:01:58,530
Wen,

11
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:01,710
Ou Xiao'an is a traitor.

12
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:04,250
You want us to believe a traitor

13
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:06,390
and that Shaotang is a mole?

14
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:12,240
It doesn't matter whether Ou Xiao'an is a traitor or not.

15
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,340
The point is

16
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,950
thousands of gas bombs are about to be released.

17
00:02:15,950 --> 00:02:17,550
It's not that serious.

18
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:20,020
Everything's under control.

19
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,990
Chief Jiang.

20
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,290
[Map of Chongqing Municipality]

21
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,970
You can't decode any of the addresses?

22
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,510
Listen, from now on,

23
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,350
you'll be on guard in shifts 24/7.

24
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:29,600
Especially the Decoding Section.

25
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,000
You'll work extra hours.

26
00:02:31,070 --> 00:02:32,590
Report to me immediately

27
00:02:32,670 --> 00:02:35,070
if you find anything about 810 or gas bombs.

28
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,160
Yes, Sir.

29
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:42,110
I have

30
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,600
good news.

31
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:47,750
[Map of Chongqing Municipality]

32
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,190
We're

33
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:46,740
ordered to

34
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,720
interrogate

35
00:02:47,820 --> 00:02:48,780
a Japanese military doctor

36
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:50,270
named Motoyoshi Ando.

37
00:02:50,690 --> 00:02:53,140
He used to work in 810.

38
00:02:53,670 --> 00:02:54,990
As soon as he's here,

39
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:57,260
we'll find out where this 810 is

40
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,100
and where those gas bombs

41
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:00,610
have been sent to.

42
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:02,500
Most importantly,

43
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,000
who the mole is

44
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:05,420
among us.

45
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,390
We'll know everything.

46
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:11,200
Like I said, everything's under control.

47
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:15,370
I hope so.

48
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,070
Welcome.

49
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:43,030
Miss.

50
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:45,470
Would you like a custom-made dress?

51
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,540
I heard that you have experienced tailors

52
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:49,100
that come from Shanghai.

53
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,579
You have good taste.

54
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,160
Our experienced tailors

55
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:54,490
are all from Shanghai.

56
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,850
They are quite skilled.

57
00:03:58,590 --> 00:04:00,500
Miss, you look chic.

58
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:01,650
Look.

59
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:04,620
These are the most popular styles now.

60
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,720
They're popular, but too many women are wearing them.

61
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:12,270
They can't make me special.

62
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:16,100
Do you have the butterfly beauty design?

63
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,930
I want it made of Nanjing Yunjin.

64
00:04:19,470 --> 00:04:21,790
We don't have a lot of it.

65
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:24,170
Our landlady has been keeping it for herself.

66
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:26,250
How about this? Have a seat.

67
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:27,590
If you really like it,

68
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,980
I'll ask the landlady for you, okay?

69
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:30,590
Thank you.

70
00:04:30,590 --> 00:04:32,050
You’re welcome. This way.

71
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,080
Miss Qin, you're here!

72
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,740
Ou Xiao'an

73
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,960
is being interrogated by the NBIS ceaselessly.

74
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,690
I found this strip of cloth in his coat

75
00:05:01,690 --> 00:05:03,090
when he was unconscious.

76
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:04,910
Obviously, he was hiding it.

77
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,770
This material doesn't look like

78
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,360
ordinary Japanese military uniforms or prison uniforms.

79
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:10,930
Yes.

80
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,310
When he was in a coma,

81
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:14,150
he kept talking about 810.

82
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,910
So I suspect

83
00:05:15,930 --> 00:05:18,530
this strip might have something to do with 810.

84
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,930
You took it secretly.

85
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:23,090
The NBIS must have known.

86
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,260
At that time,

87
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:27,060
I wasn't sure about his identity.

88
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:28,920
I wasn't sure if he was gonna wake up.

89
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,180
Even if he did,

90
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,410
I wasn't sure

91
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,310
I could get anything

92
00:05:32,310 --> 00:05:34,570
out of him without knowing his identity.

93
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:35,610
So I had to take the risk

94
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,010
and bring it to you.

95
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,190
I thought maybe this strip

96
00:05:39,220 --> 00:05:41,270
would lead us to 810.

97
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:45,430
I'm not blaming you.

98
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:49,950
I know you're worried about me.

99
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:50,870
But back in Myanmar,

100
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:52,870
that was the closest I'd been to 810.

101
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,300
I didn’t want to miss

102
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,730
any opportunity.

103
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:58,040
Yes, I wasn’t cautious enough.

104
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:59,730
But I never thought

105
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:01,350
Ou Xiao'an was from the NBIS.

106
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,110
If this strip

107
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:08,950
is really related to 810,

108
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,980
Ou Xiao'an will definitely look for it

109
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:12,100
when he wakes up.

110
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,820
I asked him about it.

111
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:16,120
But he can't remember anything

112
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,970
that happened after 1941.

113
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,500
Even if he remembers it later,

114
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,660
he was in the jungle for so long

115
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:22,320
before he was saved.

116
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,100
He can't be sure

117
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:25,100
he lost this strip after he met me.

118
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,480
Don't worry.

119
00:06:29,070 --> 00:06:30,210
Things are chaotic now.

120
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:32,590
It's already hard for you to be undercover alone.

121
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:35,220
You need to protect yourself first.

122
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,510
Don't worry, Qiushui.

123
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,760
I can handle it.

124
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:39,050
Have a seat.

125
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,870
In your opinion,

126
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:44,430
is there any medical explanation

127
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:46,090
for Ou Xiao'an's memory loss?

128
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,500
His head was severely injured.

129
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,350
It's possible that he lost his memory.

130
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,470
But medically,

131
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:53,550
nothing is 100% sure.

132
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:55,590
So I still need to investigate

133
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,150
his connection with 810.

134
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,270
What do you think

135
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:03,550
about Ou Xiao'an?

136
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:06,350
He nearly died.

137
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:08,210
There are many mysteries about him.

138
00:07:08,210 --> 00:07:10,350
The three director generals are also involved.

139
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:11,380
In the Chongqing Station,

140
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,980
he is a hot potato.

141
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,880
But I think

142
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:15,930
he’s the key

143
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,740
for us to find 810.

144
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:21,140
He's probably one of us.

145
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:25,060
One of us?

146
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,800
Comrade Mingyuan

147
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:30,510
informed me and Secretary Chen

148
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:32,470
about recruiting Ou Xiao'an.

149
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:33,890
But shortly afterwards,

150
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:36,300
Comrade Mingyuan died for our beliefs.

151
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,810
So we're not sure

152
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,390
if Ou Xiao'an

153
00:07:39,409 --> 00:07:40,980
is now one of us.

154
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:45,990
That explains it.

155
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:51,150
Secretary Chen and Ou Xiao'an

156
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:52,770
were caught by Ohashi together.

157
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:53,880
They disappeared together.

158
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:54,790
If they both had been kept in 810

159
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:56,350
all these years

160
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,590
and he managed to escape,

161
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:58,590
does that mean...

162
00:07:58,610 --> 00:08:00,670
Secretary Chen might still be alive.

163
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,920
Secretary Chen...

164
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:13,520
Moqing.

165
00:08:14,110 --> 00:08:15,670
You were young.

166
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,280
And the organization clearly stated

167
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:19,840
that it wasn't your fault.

168
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:25,850
Qiushui.

169
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:33,960
[April 1941, Shanghai]

170
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,670
Mr. Ye was seen

171
00:08:27,670 --> 00:08:29,020
because he was trying to save me.

172
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:30,830
The Japanese found out about it,

173
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:33,620
which led to the big manhunt in those days.

174
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,370
Now it seems

175
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,960
the kidnapping of Secretary Chen

176
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,760
is a conspiracy of the Japanese.

177
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,809
It has nothing to do with you.

178
00:08:43,659 --> 00:08:44,990
Don't beat yourself up.

179
00:09:02,930 --> 00:09:04,150
Hurry up.

180
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:04,990
Come on.

181
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,840
Give me that cheongsam.

182
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:08,340
-A freeloader? -That's the one.

183
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:09,300
Gosh.

184
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:11,570
Miss, where have you been?

185
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:12,820
Your brother has been looking for you.

186
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:15,100
Where is Zhang? He didn't pick you up?

187
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:18,030
Zhang is sick. I told him to go home.

188
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,330
What?

189
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:19,950
Does he have to

190
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:20,830
be sick now?

191
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:21,610
Enough.

192
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,350
What are you doing with all those things?

193
00:09:24,350 --> 00:09:26,350
We're packing. You should hurry up.

194
00:09:26,370 --> 00:09:27,550
-Go. -Go upstairs and pack.

195
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:29,480
Why are you packing out of a sudden?

196
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,310
Where have you been?

197
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:35,110
I'm an adult.

198
00:09:35,110 --> 00:09:36,990
Can you leave me alone?

199
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,380
I don't have to tell you.

200
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:40,160
How dare you talk to me like that?

201
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,490
Where are your manners?

202
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,750
Did you go to

203
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:47,310
another gathering

204
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:48,920
that Ye Xuanmin called?

205
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:53,310
How many times have I told you

206
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:54,950
not to get involved in those students' movements?

207
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:55,510
They are

208
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:57,350
all ignorant brats.

209
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:01,610
They're not brats.

210
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:02,910
They are patriots.

211
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,120
They are not like you.

212
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,280
What patriots?

213
00:10:05,620 --> 00:10:07,160
They just write some articles

214
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:07,940
and shout some slogans.

215
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,110
The provisions I donated

216
00:10:09,110 --> 00:10:10,530
during the Battle of Shanghai

217
00:10:10,530 --> 00:10:12,510
is enough to feed our family for several lifetimes.

218
00:10:12,510 --> 00:10:14,330
And I've never shouted a single slogan.

219
00:10:14,330 --> 00:10:15,610
So what?

220
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:18,320
That's not patriotism at all.

221
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,480
You were just afraid.

222
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,480
You were leaving yourself a way out.

223
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,120
-Miss. -Master.

224
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,720
Please stop talking. There's no need to be mad.

225
00:10:29,690 --> 00:10:31,810
-Cut it out. -Stop it.

226
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:35,630
I've spoiled you.

227
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:37,070
If it wasn't for me

228
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:37,890
to protect you,

229
00:10:37,890 --> 00:10:39,880
you'd have died plenty of times.

230
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:41,830
It's better than being a coward.

231
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,120
Things have been intense in Shanghai recently.

232
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,670
The Japanese used to be easy to deal with.

233
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:52,740
We could just bribed them.

234
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,500
That traitor, Zeng Jiwu

235
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,580
wanted me to cooperate with him. I refused.

236
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:59,640
Then he immediately went to the casino to make arrests.

237
00:11:01,490 --> 00:11:03,490
Do you know what I was doing just now?

238
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,070
[Kempeitai Shanghai Headquarters, Exit-Entry Permit]

239
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,460
Permit.

240
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:09,830
[Kempeitai Shanghai Headquarters, Exit-Entry Permit]

241
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,250
Mo Qing, don't worry.

242
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:18,030
I will never be a traitor.

243
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,310
I will never betray my country,

244
00:11:20,310 --> 00:11:22,510
even if I become nobody.

245
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:25,950
We talked about moving to Chongqing.

246
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,490
Now it's time.

247
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,400
Now?

248
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,550
The day after tomorrow.

249
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:31,790
Pack your things.

250
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:33,090
The three of you will take the train to Wuhan.

251
00:11:33,090 --> 00:11:33,690
Okay.

252
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:35,880
There will be someone to take you to Chongqing.

253
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:36,800
The rest of you

254
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:39,110
will leave with me and Moqing

255
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,120
by boat.

256
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:42,240
Yes, Master.

257
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:42,930
Master,

258
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,490
they're still making my cheongsam.

259
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:46,490
The clock is ticking. Just leave it.

260
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:50,170
What are you waiting for? Pack my things.

261
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,510
Hurry up! Come here!

262
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:23,350
Mr. Matsuda.

263
00:12:24,330 --> 00:12:25,180
Yes.

264
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,510
Thank you, Mr. Matsuda.

265
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:30,740
Otherwise, my family wouldn't be able to go to Chongqing.

266
00:12:31,710 --> 00:12:33,430
Yes, Mr. Matsuda.

267
00:12:34,450 --> 00:12:36,250
I’ll leave my filature business

268
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:38,370
to your family.

269
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,130
Don't mention it.

270
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:42,970
It's nothing.

271
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:45,130
Yes.

272
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,530
I'll do my best.

273
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:49,320
Yes.

274
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:52,390
Yes.

275
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:56,100
Okay.

276
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:58,480
Not at all.

277
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,840
It's a token of my appreciation.

278
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:02,490
Yes.

279
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,500
I'll take care of it.

280
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:07,650
Yes.

281
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,380
I want to burn incense to our parents.

282
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,060
[Kempeitai Shanghai Headquarters, Exit-Entry Permit]

283
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,360
Sis,

284
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:33,720
what you hear and see

285
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,670
may not be what you think it is.

286
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:43,860
Are you still mad at me?

287
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,850
